cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.DC

The paper deals with proactive tile-based video streaming for wireless virtual reality, which involves tasks related to multimedia (MM), networking and internet architecture (NI), computer vision and pattern recognition (CV), graphics (GR), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC). The paper focuses on jointly optimizing the duration of tile prediction, computing, and communication to maximize the quality of experience (QoE) of VR streaming, which involves a combination of these subfields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.CV, cs.GR, and cs.DC.
